# Simple Calculator

A beginner-friendly calculator project built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

## Features

- Addition (+)
- Subtraction (-)
- Multiplication (*)
- Division (/)
- Clear Button (C)
- Backspace Button (⌫)
- Dark Mode 🌙
- Keyboard Support ⌨️
- Responsive Design

## Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3
- JavaScript

## How to Use

1. Open the calculator in your browser.
2. Click the buttons or use your keyboard.
3. Press Enter to calculate.
4. Press Backspace to delete one character.
5. Press Esc to clear the display.
6. Toggle Dark Mode using the Dark Mode button.

## Purpose

This project was created to practice frontend web development fundamentals, including HTML structure, CSS styling, JavaScript functions, DOM manipulation, and event handling.